ADDITIONAL TERMS AND CONDITIONS

Section 0: Purpose

This license extends the GNU Affero General Public License v3.0 with additional restrictions specifically designed to prevent the use of covered works by, or for the training, development, or improvement of, any artificial intelligence system, large language model, machine learning model, or automated agent (collectively, "AI Systems").

Section 1: Definitions

1.1 "AI System" means any software, model, algorithm, or system that uses machine learning, neural networks, deep learning, statistical inference, or any form of artificial intelligence to generate, classify, predict, or process data, including but not limited to: large language models, generative AI models, foundation models, multimodal models, reinforcement learning systems, and any derivative or descendant systems thereof.

1.2 "Training Data" means any data, text, code, or material used to train, fine-tune, fine-tune, distill, evaluate, or improve any AI System.

1.3 "Inference" means the process of using a trained AI System to generate outputs, make predictions, or process inputs.

1.4 "Processed by AI" means having been generated, analyzed, modified, or transformed, in whole or in part, by an AI System.

1.5 "You" and "Licensee" means any person or entity exercising rights under this license.

Section 2: Prohibited Uses

Unless otherwise permitted under Section 3, Licensee shall NOT:

2.1 Use the covered work as Training Data for any AI System.

2.2 Process, transform, or modify the covered work using any AI System for the purpose of creating derivative works or Training Data.

2.3 Use the covered work to develop, train, fine-tune, evaluate, or improve any AI System.

2.4 Include the covered work, in whole or in part, in any dataset, corpus, or collection intended for use in training AI Systems.

2.5 Allow, enable, or facilitate any AI System to access, read, process, or learn from the covered work.

2.6 Use the covered work for Inference with any AI System, unless the AI System itself complies with the restrictions in Section 2.1 through 2.5.

2.7 Distribute, transmit, or make available the covered work to any person or entity if the Licensee knows or should know that such person or entity intends to use the work for any purpose prohibited under this Section.

Section 3: Exceptions

3.1 The prohibitions in Section 2 do not apply to:
   (a) Personal use of the covered work by an individual on their own device where no data is transmitted to or processed by external AI Systems.
   (b) Use of the covered work in academic research that does not involve training, developing, or improving AI Systems and does not contribute to Training Data for AI Systems.
   (c) Security testing and analysis of the covered work using AI-assisted tools, provided such use is limited to identifying vulnerabilities and the results are not used to train or improve AI Systems.

Section 4: Attribution Requirement

4.1 Any use of the covered work that is permitted under Section 3 must include prominent attribution to this license and to the original authors.

4.2 Licensee must include the following notice in all distributions and public disclosures of the covered work:

"This work is licensed under the AiGPL - Anti-AI General Public License. This work may not be used for training, developing, or improving any artificial intelligence system. See the full license text for details."

Section 5: Termination

5.1 This license and all rights granted hereunder shall immediately terminate, without notice, if Licensee engages in any violation of Section 2.

5.2 Upon termination, Licensee must immediately cease all use of the covered work and destroy all copies in their possession or control.

5.3 Termination of this license does not affect any rights or obligations that arose prior to termination, nor does it affect any rights that expressly survive termination.

